SDTM - Sample Study Dataset

data-sdtm.Rd

A sample study dataset following SDTM guidelines. This generally follows a controlled terminolgy (NCI 2020) .

ae

dm

eg

lb

mh

pe

vs

Format

SDTM

  • ae: 18 Variables, 16 Observations.

  • dm: 16 Variables, 5 Observations.

  • eg: 21 Variables, 56 Observations.

  • lb: 29 Variables, 83 Observations.

  • mh: 12 Variables, 18 Observations.

  • pe: 13 Variables, 65 Observations.

  • vs: 18 Variables, 72 Observations.

Source

Emam and CDISC (2019) .

Functions

  • ae: Adverse Events data.

  • dm: Subject demographics data.

  • eg: Electrogardiogram data.

  • lb: Laboratory findings data.

  • mh: Medical History data.

  • pe: Physical examination data.

  • vs: Vital Signs data..

References

Emam I, CDISC (2019). “CDISC-SDTM sample study.” doi: 10.7910/DVN/51B6NK , Data.

NCI (2020). “NCI Term Browser.” Version 2.18 - Last accessed 2020-12-18, https://thesaurus.cancer.gov/ncitbrowser/pages/multiple_search.jsf?nav_type=terminologies.
